cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.DC 

This paper is about a framework for analyzing Android applications, which is related to computer security (cs.CR) as it focuses on malware analysis. It also involves software engineering (cs.SE) as it provides an interface for the development of plugins and emphasizes adaptability and expandability. The framework itself is implemented in Python, which is a programming language (cs.PL). Additionally, the framework includes an abstraction layer for phone event simulation, which is related to systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of dynamic analysis methods, which is related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
